      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see. so if the statistics show those specific groups have much higher rates of violent crime, some researchers argue that the raw data suggests an inherent likelihood or behavioral tendency that's distinct from just being poor. how do scholars typically address the argument that these crime trends are actually indicative of group-specific traits rather than just environmental factors?",
